headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet made two 3-pointers in overtime and scored 25 points, and the Toronto Raptors beat the Washington Wizards 116-109 on Saturday to split their two-game series.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fred VanVleet hits 2 3s in OT, Raptors beat Wizards 116-109

headlines.description: — Darius Garland had 21 points and seven assists, Donovan Mitchell scored 20 points and the Cleveland Cavaliers led by 35 points in a 114-90 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garland scores 21 points, Cavaliers rout Pistons 114-90

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo scored 30 points and the Miami Heat held Trae Young to a season-low eight points in a 117-109 victory over the Atlanta Hawks on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Adebayo scores 30, Young has season-low 8 as Heat beat Hawks

events.name: Houston Rockets at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Tari Eason matched his season high with 20 points and the Houston Rockets ended an 11-game losing streak, beating the San Antonio Spurs 122-110 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: NBA-worst Rockets beat Spurs to end 11-game losing streak
76ers rally to win 133-130, snap Bucks' 16-game streak

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 27 points and the Minnesota Timberwolves beat Sacramento 138-134 on Saturday night to snap the Kings' winning streak at five games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Edwards scores 27 points, Timberwolves edge Kings
